Platform Buddy v165

Summary:
- Reworked VBT Studio into a wizard-style flow instead of showing trim, plate settings, ROI controls, analysis, and result in one long panel.
- New flow: trim video -> auto plate detection beta -> confirm plate / manual adjust -> set info confirmation -> analyzing -> result.
- Added auto plate detection beta using a browser-side frame heuristic. It proposes an ROI candidate first and only exposes manual ROI adjustment when needed.
- Added wizard step state and UI helpers: setVbtWizardStep, updateVbtWizardChrome, runAutoPlateDetection, detectPlateCandidateFromFrame, confirmAutoDetectedPlate, showManualPlateSelection.
- Kept existing plate ROI tracking, rep detection, Hero result, velocity loss, and Buddy judgement logic intact.
- Kept manual 2-point fallback inside the set information step as an emergency route.
- Added v165 wizard CSS for step screens, progress dots, loading screen, sticky mobile actions, and set summary card.
- Updated PWA cache/query versions to v165.

Files changed:
- index.html
  - Updated asset query versions to v165.

- styles.css
  - Added VBT wizard layout styles.
  - Added active/hidden step screen behavior.
  - Added wizard loading state and progress styles.
  - Added mobile-first sticky action area.

- video.js
  - Added VBT wizard step management.
  - Replaced long VBT Studio panel with separate wizard screens.
  - Added auto plate detection beta before manual ROI.
  - Added confirm/manual plate route.
  - Move result display to its own screen.
  - On analysis success or failure, the UI now moves to the result screen.

- sw.js
  - Updated CACHE_NAME and cached URLs to v165.

- manifest.webmanifest
  - Updated start_url to ./index.html?v=165.

Known notes:
- The auto plate detection is a lightweight browser heuristic, not a trained AI model.
- If auto detection is low confidence or fails, the manual plate screen remains available.
- Existing VBT calculation and storage structure were not intentionally redesigned in this patch.
